post.description:
Stop Analytics DB Synchronization



The following API stop the synchronization of analytics DB. After the user calls this API the analytics DB will be static until the next call to start initialization API

This API can be called when analytics DB deployment state is: [DEPLOYED] and run state is: [ACTIVE_SYNC_ON].

After this API is called the run state will be changed to: [ACTIVE_SYNC_OFF]



This API requires **DMS_STOP_ANALYTICS_DB_SYNCHRONIZATION** permission(s).

400.description:
Code : ANALYTICS_DB_MUST_BE_DEPLOYED, Details: []

Code : ANALYTICS_DB_ORIGIN_RUN_STATE_INVALID, Details: [validOriginStates, currentRunState]

200.description:
The below table describes the response parameters:

| Parameter   |Type   |Description          | Example   |
|-------------|-------|---------------------|-----------|
|runState|string|The run state of the analytics DB Values:INACTIVE,INITIALIZING,STOPPING_INITIALIZATION,ACTIVE_SYNC_ON,ACTIVE_SYNC_OFF|INACTIVE|
|deploymentState|string|The deployment state of the analytics DB Values:NOT_DEPLOYED,DEPLOYED|NOT_DEPLOYED|
|lastModifiedTime|string|A UTC date-time in the ISO-8601 format|2007-12-20T10:15:30Z|
|creationTime|string|A UTC date-time in the ISO-8601 format|2007-12-20T10:15:30Z|

post.description:
Stop Analytics DB Initialization



The following API stop the process of creating analytics DB.

This API can be called when analytics DB deployment state is: [DEPLOYED] and run state is: [INITIALIZING].

After this API is called the run state will be changed to: [STOPPING_INITIALIZATION] and when the analytics DB initialization process is stopped completely the state will be: [INACTIVE]



This API requires **DMS_STOP_ANALYTICS_DB_INITIALIZATION** permission(s).

400.description:
Code : ANALYTICS_DB_MUST_BE_DEPLOYED, Details: []

Code : ANALYTICS_DB_ORIGIN_RUN_STATE_INVALID, Details: [validOriginStates, currentRunState]

200.description:
The below table describes the response parameters:

| Parameter   |Type   |Description          | Example   |
|-------------|-------|---------------------|-----------|
|runState|string|The run state of the analytics DB Values:INACTIVE,INITIALIZING,STOPPING_INITIALIZATION,ACTIVE_SYNC_ON,ACTIVE_SYNC_OFF|INACTIVE|
|deploymentState|string|The deployment state of the analytics DB Values:NOT_DEPLOYED,DEPLOYED|NOT_DEPLOYED|
|lastModifiedTime|string|A UTC date-time in the ISO-8601 format|2007-12-20T10:15:30Z|
|creationTime|string|A UTC date-time in the ISO-8601 format|2007-12-20T10:15:30Z|

post.description:
Start Analytics DB Initialization



The following API start the process of creating analytics DB. After the process is finished the analytics DB will be available for queries.

This API can be called when analytics DB deployment state is: [DEPLOYED] and run state is: [INACTIVE, ACTIVE_SYNC_OFF].

After this API is called the run state will be changed to: [INITIALIZING] and when the analytics DB initialization process is finished the state will be: [ACTIVE_SYNC_ON]



This API requires **DMS_START_ANALYTICS_DB_INITIALIZATION** permission(s).

400.description:
Code : ANALYTICS_DB_MUST_BE_DEPLOYED, Details: []

Code : ANALYTICS_DB_ORIGIN_RUN_STATE_INVALID, Details: [validOriginStates, currentRunState]

get.description: Search Report entities by filter Returns list of Report, the response can be filtered, sorted and supports pagination **For more information and examples on creating search requests, click here.** ## Filter Each additionalProp can filter one field, inside additionalProp there are many optional conditions that can be used for filtering that field By using the logical additionalProps $AND, $OR, $NOT, you can add complex nested logic filters. When sending these props, you must send only the nested filter field inside the filter value. This will allow you to group additional filters using logical AND/OR/NOT operators. When not sending a logic prop (including when not sending a nested logic prop), the props are bundled together using logical AND operators, this means that only the items that match all filter conditions for that field will be returned. ***filter*** items possible values: [ *id*,*callbackEndpoint*,*status*,*maxFileSizeInBytes*,*fullReference*,*lastModifiedTime*,*creationTime*,*name*,*reportInitiator.userId*,*reportInitiator.ownerOrganizationId*,*reportInitiator.userEntityType*,*reportInitiator.templateId* ] ## Sort Results can be sorted by multiple fields, the order of the fields in the sort request governs the hierarchy of the sort The first field is the primary sort, the second is used when two values of the first field are the same, and so forth ***sort.order*** default value is DESC ***sort.prop*** possible values:[ *id*,*callbackEndpoint*,*name*,*status*,*maxFileSizeInBytes*,*fullReference*,*lastModifiedTime*,*creationTime* ] If sort was not specified, the result will be sorted by: creationTime DESC ## Free text search When freeTextSearch is passed, the free text search will be performed on every field except those of type Date If used together with filters, freeTextSearch will be bundled to the filters with the logical AND operator, this means that only items that match all filters (and each filter's conditions) and the free text search will be returned ## Page ***limit*** max number of results that will be returned for each page. If not specify, the default will be 100 ***page*** page number starting from 0. If not specify, the default will be 0 ## Build URL Encode the JSON object and use the encoded string as the searchRequest parameter: https://<URL>?searchRequest= Query Parameters: | Parameter |Type | Mandatory| Description | Example | |-------------|-------|----------|----------------------|-----------| |searchRequest||false|Search request parameters: filter, sort and page|| This API requires **PROTECTED_API** permission(s).

runState.description: The run state of the analytics DB

deploymentState.description: The deployment state of the analytics DB

lastModifiedTime.description: A UTC date-time in the ISO-8601 format

creationTime.description: A UTC date-time in the ISO-8601 format

filter.description: Each additionalProp can filter one field, inside additionalProp there are many optional conditions that can be used for filtering that field. When multiple conditions are specified, they are bundled together using logical AND operators, this means that only the items that match all filter conditions for that field will be returned

sort.description: Results can be sorted by multiple fields, the order of the fields in the sort request governs the hierarchy of the sort.The first field is the primary sort, the second is used when two values of the first field are the same, and so forth

freeTextSearch.description: Free text search strings - will be bundled to the filters with the logical AND operator. Possible to pass a few strings with space between them, the search will return a result if one of strings appears in the data entity (OR operator).

sort.description: Sort that was passed in the request

filter.description: The filter that was passed in the request

freeTextSearch.description: Free text search strings that was passed in the request

totalResults.description: The total number of items that match the query

data.description: List of items that match the search request
